<item>
 <title>LoL = Lexicon of Lust</title>
 <link>https://www.mererid.co.uk/node/43</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;One of my works, &#039;Whites colour chart&#039;, was accepted into this exhibition for Fringe arts Bath, opening this Friday evening. Since the work has proved popular I decided to make a limited edition of 11. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This was the callout/description of the exhibition:&lt;br /&gt;
LoL = Lexicon of Lust&lt;br /&gt;
In Art we feel that meaning has become meaningless. Or do we - perhaps we don&#039;t mean that? We welcome work that is playful, ambiguous, theatrical, dystopian, humorous, contrarian and perhaps even alludes to the figurative. A good title will go a long way. No paintings, drawings or performances thank you - just &#039;things&#039; that we can &#039;lust&#039; over.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Where:    FaB 1, 94-96 Walcot Street, Bath BA1 5BG&lt;br /&gt;
Launch:   25 May open 6pm &#039;til late - #FaB18 Opening Night Arty Party&lt;br /&gt;
When:     10am to 6pm daily - 26 May to 10 June&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fringeartsbath.co.uk/2018-exhibitions/&quot;&gt;https://www.fringeartsbath.co.uk/2018-exhibitions/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-image field-type-image field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.mererid.co.uk/sites/mererid.co.uk/files/styles/large/public/blog/images/lexicon%20of%20lust%20poster%20small.jpg?itok=1R2WU5m3&quot; width=&quot;480&quot; height=&quot;339&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
